- Scala has two kinds of variables. var and val

- val : is for value. similar to final variable in java. 
        a val can never be reassigned.

  > val msg = "Hello World!"

- var : is for variable. A var can be reassigned throughtput its lifetime

- in Scala, variables types are specify after variable name, separated by a colon.

  > val msg: String = "Hello World!"
